	<h2>Sub-optimal Configuration Detected</h2>
</div>
TPL_REQUIRE_2
<div id="wrap">
	<p>Loopstream will broadcast in "CD Quality", meaning a level of detail
	<br />(samplerate) of 44100Hz. Some of your audio devices use a different samplerate.</p>
	
	<hr />
	
	<p class="l">This means two things.</p>
	
	<ol>
		<li>You never hear your music in full quality,
			<br />since windows is "resampling" (converting) your music</li>
	
		<li>Loopstream will have to do the same, meaning:
		<ul>
			<li>sound quality is lowered further</li>
			<li>there will be a 2 second delay</li>
			<li>more load on your computer
		</ul></li>
	</ol>
	<p style="margin:-.5em">&nbsp;</p>
	
	<p>I can help you configure your sound card correctly.</p>
	<p>Wanna do that?</p>

	<div id="devs">
		<a href="/page/resample">Fix soundcard samplerate</a>
		<a href="/page/done?serv">Continue with lower quality</a>
	</div>
</div>
